<subSubSection lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,1912,2016]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1912,1938]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Etymology</emphasis>
: Named for the collector, J.G. Theron, who published taxonomic papers on leafhoppers between 1970–1988.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,1912,2016]" lastBlockId="33.[151,1436,152,951]" lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,466,1990,2016]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">External morphology</emphasis>
. Vertex with disc smooth, anterior margin shagreened. Clypeus light brown with ochraceous horizontal arcs. Clypellus broad, 1.3 times as long as wide, tapering apically. Pronotum without carina. Submacropter with tegmina with three anteapical cells, four narrow apical cells, reduced appendix; hind wing about half as long as tegmina, jugal lobe present, folded over anal area. Macropters rare, with hind wing as long as tegmina. Profemur with short, stout setae in row AV, about 8 long, fine intercalary setae, one AM1 seta. Protibial setal formula 1+4; mesotibial setal formula 4+4; metafemur setal formula 2+2+1, with median pair consisting of one robust, long seta, one fine, short seta.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,152,951]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,390,383,409]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Genital capsule</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[405,468,383,409]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Male</emphasis>
. Aedeagus extremely long, narrow, flattened laterally; extending into tergite VIII, sometimes into tergite VII; gonopore subapical, dorsal (
<figureCitation box="[821,992,422,448]" captionStart="FIGURES 284–290" captionStartId="55.[151,271,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[260,1328,188,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-65@55.[208,1377,138,1856]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURES 284–290. Theronus priapus. Fig. 284, aedeagus, ventral view; Fig. 285, aedeagus, lateral view; Fig. 286, plate and valve; Fig. 287, apex of abdomen, dorsal view, depicting position of genitalia; Fig. 288, style; Fig. 289, sternite VII, female; Fig. 290, apex of abdomen, lateral view, depicting position of genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5363535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5363535/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs 284, 285</figureCitation>
). Connective linear, arms fused (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 284–290" captionStartId="55.[151,271,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[260,1328,188,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-65@55.[208,1377,138,1856]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURES 284–290. Theronus priapus. Fig. 284, aedeagus, ventral view; Fig. 285, aedeagus, lateral view; Fig. 286, plate and valve; Fig. 287, apex of abdomen, dorsal view, depicting position of genitalia; Fig. 288, style; Fig. 289, sternite VII, female; Fig. 290, apex of abdomen, lateral view, depicting position of genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5363535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5363535/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 284</figureCitation>
). Plate about half length of pygofer; apex denticulate (
<figureCitation box="[856,962,461,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 284–290" captionStartId="55.[151,271,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[260,1328,188,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-65@55.[208,1377,138,1856]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURES 284–290. Theronus priapus. Fig. 284, aedeagus, ventral view; Fig. 285, aedeagus, lateral view; Fig. 286, plate and valve; Fig. 287, apex of abdomen, dorsal view, depicting position of genitalia; Fig. 288, style; Fig. 289, sternite VII, female; Fig. 290, apex of abdomen, lateral view, depicting position of genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5363535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5363535/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 286</figureCitation>
). Anal tube superficial, not invaginated into pygofer. Pygofer lobe setose, posterior margin uniformly rounded; in dorsal view acutely triangular (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 284–290" captionStartId="55.[151,271,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[260,1328,188,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-65@55.[208,1377,138,1856]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURES 284–290. Theronus priapus. Fig. 284, aedeagus, ventral view; Fig. 285, aedeagus, lateral view; Fig. 286, plate and valve; Fig. 287, apex of abdomen, dorsal view, depicting position of genitalia; Fig. 288, style; Fig. 289, sternite VII, female; Fig. 290, apex of abdomen, lateral view, depicting position of genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5363535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5363535/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs 287, 290</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,152,951]" box="[197,1285,576,603]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,390,576,602]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Genital capsule</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[404,495,576,602]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Female</emphasis>
. Pygofer with numerous macrosetae, ovipositor as long as pygofer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,152,951]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,369,615,641]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Relationships</emphasis>
. This genus is a typical member of the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dallas" authorityYear="1870" box="[909,1084,616,642]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Deltocephalini">Deltocephalini</taxonomicName>
that is defined by having the connective fused to the aedeagus (
<bibRefCitation author="Zahniser &amp; Dietrich" box="[555,871,654,680]" firstAuthor="Zahniser" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref38641" refString="Zahniser, J. N. &amp; Dietrich, C. H. (2008) Phylogeny of the leafhopper subfamily Deltocephalinae (Insecta: Auchenorrhyncha: Cicadellidae) and related subfamilies based on morphology. Systematics and Biodiversity, 6 (1), 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="2008">Zahniser &amp; Dietrich, 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ossiannilsson" box="[884,1125,654,680]" firstAuthor="Ossiannilsson" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="594 - 978" refId="ref38021" refString="Ossiannilsson, F. (1983) The Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica, 7 (3), 594 - 978." type="journal article" year="1983">Ossiannilsson, 1983</bibRefCitation>
). It is characterized by the male genitalia that are so large that they extend into abdominal segment VIII or even VII, and have the aedeagus blade-like and curved ventroposteriorly. This genus is not closely related to any Afrotropical genus in this tribe such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Edwards. Occasionally" authorityName="Edwards. Occasionally" authorityYear="1922" box="[382,742,770,796]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Recilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[382,465,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Recilia</emphasis>
Edwards. Occasionally
</taxonomicName>
, however, similar colouration is found in pale specimens of species of genera such as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Theron (Theron" authorityYear="1975" box="[474,612,809,834]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pravistylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[474,612,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Pravistylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Theron. The" authorityYear="1975" box="[674,776,809,834]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Vilargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[674,776,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Vilargus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that are in the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1908" box="[1033,1181,809,835]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Paralimnini">Paralimnini</taxonomicName>
. No genera from the Palaearctic Region bearing any genitalic resemblance were listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ossiannilsson" box="[971,1222,848,874]" firstAuthor="Ossiannilsson" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="594 - 978" refId="ref38021" refString="Ossiannilsson, F. (1983) The Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica, 7 (3), 594 - 978." type="journal article" year="1983">Ossiannilsson (1983)</bibRefCitation>
or 
<bibRefCitation author="Ribaut" box="[1263,1431,848,874]" firstAuthor="Ribaut" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 474" refId="ref38051" refString="Ribaut, H. (1952) Homopteres Auchenorhynques. II (Jassidae). Faune de France, 57, 1 - 474." type="journal article" year="1952">Ribaut (1952)</bibRefCitation>
, although some bear similar external features, such as colour and shape. 
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori" box="[986,1200,886,912]" firstAuthor="Linnavuori" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 370" refId="ref37750" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1959) Revision of the Neotropical Deltocephalinae and some related subfamilies (Homoptera). Annales Zoologici Societatis Zoologicae Botanicae Fennicae ' Vanamo', 20 (1), 1 - 370." type="journal article" year="1959">Linnavuori (1959)</bibRefCitation>
described a number of genera from the Nearctic Region in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dallas" authorityYear="1870" box="[647,822,925,951]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Deltocephalini">Deltocephalini</taxonomicName>
, but none show any relationship with 
<emphasis box="[1267,1384,925,950]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2009" box="[1267,1380,925,950]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Theronus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Theronus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
